---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CtaBanner from '../../components/CtaBanner.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="701am — Earned Media for Startups"
  description="A startup's scarcest asset isn't capital — it's attention. Earned media that turns your founder's story and your traction into the press that recruits, raises, and sells, without a paid budget you don't have."
  breadcrumbs={[
    { name: 'Industries', url: '/industries' },
    { name: 'Startups' },
  ]}
>

  <!-- ════ HERO ════ -->
  <section class="hero" id="top">
    <div class="hero-grain" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="hero-rays" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="hero-sun" aria-hidden="true"></div>

    <div class="hero-content">
      <p class="hero-overline">
        <span class="hero-overline-rule"></span>
        Industries · For startups
        <span class="hero-overline-rule"></span>
      </p>

      <h1 class="hero-headline">
        You can't outspend them.<br />You can <em>out-story</em> them.
      </h1>

      <p class="hero-deck">
        A startup is outgunned on budget by every incumbent in the category. The one advantage you have is a sharper story and a faster-moving truth. <em>Earned media is the lever that turns that story into the attention you cannot afford to buy.</em>
      </p>

      <div class="cta-cluster">
        <a class="btn-primary" href="/discovery">
          Book a sunrise call
          <span class="btn-icon" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        </a>
        <a class="btn-link" href="#method">
          See how it works
          <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">↓</span>
        </a>
      </div>

      <p class="cta-fine">Thirty minutes. No deck. No pitch. No charge.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ PRESS STRIP ════ -->
  <section class="press-strip" aria-label="Where the startup story gets told">
    <div class="press-inner">
      <p class="press-label">
        <span class="press-star">★</span>
        Where the startup story gets told
        <span class="press-star">★</span>
      </p>
      <div class="press-logos">
        <span class="press-logo press-TECHCRUNCH">condensed</span>
        <span class="press-logo press-Forbes">italic</span>
        <span class="press-logo press-Inc.">roman</span>
        <span class="press-logo press-BUSINESS INSIDER">condensed</span>
        <span class="press-logo press-Fast Company">italic</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § 01 — THE FIRST TRUTH ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy">
    <div class="container reveal">
      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ 01 · The first truth</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2">Capital is borrowed.<br /><em>Attention is earned.</em></h2>
      <div class="body">
        <p class="dropcap">
          Every startup pitches the same arc: big market, bold team, inevitable future. An investor, a recruit, a first customer — they hear that arc a hundred times a month, so they discount the pitch and look for the one signal a founder cannot manufacture: <em>does the world outside your deck believe you yet.</em>
        </p>

        <div class="aphorism">The story is the moat before the product is</div>

        <p>
          That belief is not bought — you do not have the budget, and the incumbents will always outspend you. It is earned when a reporter covering your space writes about <strong>you</strong>, when your founder's contrarian take runs where investors and recruits read, when your name is the one a customer brings up before you pitch them.
        </p>

        <p>
          The proof is in your own trajectory right now. The traction curve no one expected. The insight that made you start the company. The wedge the incumbents are too slow to see. Each is a story a tech reporter is hunting for and <em>cannot get from a Series-D incumbent.</em> Most founders wait until they're 'ready.' The ones who break out place the story while it is still surprising.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § 02 — THE LEDGER ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy ledger-section">
    <div class="container-wide reveal">
      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ 02 · The ledger</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2">What an earned placement <em>does for a desk.</em></h2>

      <div class="ledger-grid">
        <div class="ledger-cell">
          <div class="ledger-num">14</div>
          <div class="ledger-cap">Placements earned</div>
          <div class="ledger-sub">Pre-Series A</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ledger-divider" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <div class="ledger-cell">
          <div class="ledger-num">3</div>
          <div class="ledger-cap">Tech outlets</div>
          <div class="ledger-sub">TechCrunch · Forbes · more</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ledger-divider" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <div class="ledger-cell">
          <div class="ledger-num">1</div>
          <div class="ledger-cap">Un-ignorable founder story</div>
          <div class="ledger-sub">Found in the first call</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ledger-prose">
        <p>
          The pattern repeats across early-stage companies. We spend the first weeks finding the angle no incumbent can claim — a founder's origin, a contrarian thesis, a traction number that breaks the pattern — and the rest placing it where investors, recruits, and customers already read. <em>The category changes. The mechanism does not.</em>
        </p>
      </div>

      <p class="ledger-coda">★ Illustrative of the pattern. Client specifics confidential. ★</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § 03 — THE METHOD ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy" id="method">
    <div class="container reveal">
      <p class="proclamation-hinge">
        The office holds the same two articles, whatever the industry on the masthead —
      </p>

      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ 03 · The method</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2 h2-dark">Two things. Done <em>without compromise.</em></h2>
      <div class="body body-dark body-center">
        <p>
          We do not run your growth experiments or write your launch tweets. We build the conditions under which an investor, a recruit, or a customer already knows your name before you reach out. <em>The method fits on a single page, and it does not bend for the stage you are at.</em>
        </p>
      </div>

      <article class="doc">
        <header class="doc-header">
          <div class="doc-stamp">★ Tenets of the office ★</div>
          <h3 class="doc-title">The Two Articles of Earned Authority</h3>
          <p class="doc-sub">Adopted at sunrise. Held for the founder's desk.</p>
        </header>

        <div class="tenet">
          <div class="tenet-mark">Art. i</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="tenet-h">Find the angle inside your story.</h4>
            <p class="tenet-p">
              Buried in your origin and your traction is one true sentence about why now that no incumbent can claim and no editor can refuse. <em>It is almost never the thing on your pitch deck's title slide.</em> We sit with you until we find it, and then we sharpen it until it cuts.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tenet">
          <div class="tenet-mark">Art. ii</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="tenet-h">Place it where it compounds.</h4>
            <p class="tenet-p">
              A launch nobody covers is a tree falling in an empty forest. We do the unglamorous work — the research, the pitch, the follow-up — until the right reporter at <em>TechCrunch</em> or <em>Forbes</em> runs the story. Then we do it again, until your name is the one the ecosystem repeats.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="doc-sig">
          <p class="doc-sig-line">— 701am, est. at sunrise</p>
          <div class="doc-sig-title">Office of Earned Media</div>
        </div>
        <div class="doc-wax">7:01</div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § 04 — THE WORK ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy" id="work">
    <div class="container-wide reveal">
      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ 04 · The work</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2">Three engagements.<br /><em>Built for the desk.</em></h2>
      <div class="body body-center">
        <p>
          Three ways the office goes to work on a startup. <em>Pick the one that fits the round you are in.</em>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="stamp-rule">
        <div class="stamp-rule-bar"></div>
        <div class="stamp-rule-time">7:01</div>
        <div class="stamp-rule-bar"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="eng-grid">
        <article class="eng-card">
          <div class="eng-num">i.</div>
          <div class="eng-tier">Engagement I · The fastest</div>
          <h3 class="eng-h">Mine the <em>founder story.</em></h3>
          <p class="eng-p">
            We turn your origin and your traction into a single reporter-ready angle on why now — the story that makes a tech editor want to write about you, not your category.
          </p>
          <ul class="eng-list">
            <li>Founder &amp; traction audit</li>
            <li>One un-ignorable thesis</li>
            <li>Reporter-ready memo</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="eng-card">
          <div class="eng-num">ii.</div>
          <div class="eng-tier">Engagement II · The campaign</div>
          <h3 class="eng-h">Own the <em>launch narrative.</em></h3>
          <p class="eng-p">
            A sustained placement campaign timed to your raise, your launch, or your wedge. Your founder becomes the named voice on the shift you are betting the company on.
          </p>
          <ul class="eng-list">
            <li>Pitch · place · follow-up</li>
            <li>TechCrunch · Forbes · Inc.</li>
            <li>Founder positioning</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="eng-card">
          <div class="eng-num">iii.</div>
          <div class="eng-tier">Engagement III · The engine</div>
          <h3 class="eng-h">Arm your <em>founding team.</em></h3>
          <p class="eng-p">
            The earned-media skills you and your team can run yourselves — pitch craft, journalist research, the angle-finder — so you are not dependent on a retainer you can't justify yet.
          </p>
          <ul class="eng-list">
            <li>Earned-media playbook</li>
            <li>Startup press list</li>
            <li>Repeatable, in-house</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ FOUNDER NOTE ════ -->
  <section class="founder-note">
    <div class="founder-inner reveal">
      <p class="founder-eyebrow">
        <span class="founder-rule"></span>
        A note from the office
        <span class="founder-rule"></span>
      </p>
      <blockquote class="founder-quote">
        There are a thousand startups with a deck that says they will win. There are perhaps a handful a reporter would write about today. <em>We are built to make you one of them — before you can afford to be.</em> If attention is your bottleneck, the sunrise call is free.
      </blockquote>
      <p class="founder-sig">
        <span class="founder-name">— David</span>
        <span class="founder-time">at 7:01</span>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § — FROM THE FIELD ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy">
    <div class="container-wide reveal">
      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ — From the field</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2">What the desk <em>hears back.</em></h2>

      <div class="field-grid">
        <figure class="field-card">
          <div class="field-mark" aria-hidden="true">&ldquo;</div>
          <blockquote class="field-quote">
            They found the angle in our founding story we kept burying under product features. The TechCrunch piece that followed brought us two term sheets.
          </blockquote>
          <figcaption class="field-by">
            <span class="field-name">Co-founder &amp; CEO</span>
            <span class="field-role">Seed-stage fintech</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure class="field-card">
          <div class="field-mark" aria-hidden="true">&ldquo;</div>
          <blockquote class="field-quote">
            We had no budget to compete on ads. One earned story did more for recruiting than six months of cold outreach.
          </blockquote>
          <figcaption class="field-by">
            <span class="field-name">Founder</span>
            <span class="field-role">Pre-Series A dev-tools company</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure class="field-card">
          <div class="field-mark" aria-hidden="true">&ldquo;</div>
          <blockquote class="field-quote">
            What I paid for was placements. What I got was a why-now thesis our investors started repeating in their own LP updates.
          </blockquote>
          <figcaption class="field-by">
            <span class="field-name">CEO</span>
            <span class="field-role">Climate-tech startup</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>

      <p class="ledger-coda">★ Names withheld where confidentiality required. Words unchanged. ★</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ CTA ════ -->
  <CtaBanner
    eyebrow="The work begins at 7:01"
    heading="Ready to <em>out-story</em> the incumbents?"
    body="Thirty minutes. We listen, find the angle hiding in your founding story, and tell you straight whether we can earn you the attention you can't yet buy."
    primaryLabel="Book a sunrise call"
    primaryHref="/discovery"
    secondaryLabel="Or read the field manual"
    secondaryHref="/legend-maker"
  />

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* ─────── WHO THIS IS FOR — buyer-segment cards (optional) ─────── */
  .aud-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 0;
    max-width: 64rem;
    margin: var(--x1) auto 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-strong);
    background: var(--rule-strong);
  }
  .aud-card {
    background: var(--paper-soft);
    padding: var(--x2) calc(var(--x2) - var(--x5));
    position: relative;
  }
  .aud-card + .aud-card { border-left: 1px solid var(--rule-strong); }
  .aud-tag {
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--claret);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 var(--x4);
  }
  .aud-h {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-feature-settings: "kern" 1, "liga" 1, "dlig" 1;
    font-size: var(--f4-size);
    line-height: 1.1;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.018em;
    margin: 0 0 var(--x4);
    text-wrap: balance;
  }
  .aud-h em { font-style: italic; font-weight: 400; color: var(--claret); }
  .aud-p {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-feature-settings: "kern" 1, "liga" 1, "onum" 1;
    font-size: var(--f6-size);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x3);
  }
  .aud-p em { font-style: italic; color: var(--claret); }
  .aud-line {
    margin: 0;
    padding-top: var(--x4);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.10em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-fainter);
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* ─────── ENGAGEMENTS — mirrors the index "offers" three-up ─────── */
  .eng-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 0;
    max-width: 64rem;
    margin: var(--x1) auto 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-strong);
    background: var(--rule-strong);
  }
  .eng-card {
    background: var(--paper-soft);
    padding: var(--x2) calc(var(--x2) - var(--x5));
    position: relative;
  }
  .eng-card + .eng-card { border-left: 1px solid var(--rule-strong); }
  .eng-num {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: var(--f3-size);
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--claret);
    font-variant-numeric: oldstyle-nums;
    margin-bottom: var(--x4);
  }
  .eng-tier {
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-fainter);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: var(--x4);
  }
  .eng-h {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-feature-settings: "kern" 1, "liga" 1, "dlig" 1;
    font-size: var(--f4-size);
    line-height: 1.12;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.018em;
    margin: 0 0 var(--x4);
    text-wrap: balance;
  }
  .eng-h em { font-style: italic; font-weight: 400; color: var(--claret); }
  .eng-p {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-feature-settings: "kern" 1, "liga" 1, "onum" 1;
    font-size: var(--f6-size);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x3);
  }
  .eng-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: var(--x4) 0 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .eng-list li {
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    padding: var(--x5) 0;
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: var(--x4);
    counter-increment: eng;
  }
  .eng-list { counter-reset: eng; }
  .eng-list li::before {
    content: counter(eng, lower-roman) ".";
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--claret);
    font-size: 12px;
    min-width: 1.4em;
  }

  /* ─────── FROM THE FIELD — mirrors the index testimonial cards ─────── */
  .field-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: var(--x3);
    max-width: 64rem;
    margin: var(--x1) auto 0;
  }
  .field-card {
    background: var(--paper-soft);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-top: 3px solid var(--claret);
    padding: var(--x2) calc(var(--x2) - var(--x5)) var(--x2);
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }
  .field-mark {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 3rem;
    line-height: 0.5;
    height: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--claret);
  }
  .field-quote {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-feature-settings: "kern" 1, "liga" 1, "onum" 1;
    font-size: var(--f6-size);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x3);
    flex: 1;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }
  .field-by {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    padding-top: var(--x4);
  }
  .field-name {
    display: block;
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: var(--f5-size);
    color: var(--claret);
    line-height: 1.2;
  }
  .field-role {
    display: block;
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-fainter);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: var(--x5);
  }

  /* ─────── RESPONSIVE ─────── */
  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .aud-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .aud-card + .aud-card { border-left: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-strong); }
    .eng-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .eng-card + .eng-card { border-left: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-strong); }
    .field-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
